<bioghist altrender="history" encodinganalog="545" id="a2">
	<head>Historical Note</head>
	<p>In 1965, the General Assembly formed the Connecticut Tax Study Commission by Public Act 461 in order to study the property tax laws with respect to personal property of business. William F. Gwinn, President of United Aircraft Corp., was the chair of the nine-member commission, and John F. Tarrant of the Tax Department served as Executive Director and Counsel. The report was dated March 1, 1967.</p>
</bioghist>
<scopecontent encodinganalog="520" id="a3">
	<head>Scope and Content</head>
	<p>Records include correspondence, working papers, drafts and the final version of the Commission’s report to the General Assembly.</p>
</scopecontent>
<relatedmaterial encodinganalog="544 1" id="a6">
	<head>Related Material</head>
	<p>RG 005:034, John Dempsey gubernatorial records, Box A-288, Property Tax (2 folders).</p>
	<p>RG 045, State Revenue Task Force, 1969-1971.</p>
	<p>RG 047, Special Tax Commission, 1932-1935.</p>
	<p>RG 076, Department of Revenue Services, Box A-356, Tax Department (3 folders).</p>
 <p>RG 077, Bipartisan Commission on State Tax Revenue and Related Fiscal Policy, 1982-1983</p>
	<p>RG 086, Governor's Commission on Tax Reform, 1972.</p> 
</relatedmaterial>

